abstract: The Jaguar produces a thrilling growl from its supercharged 5-liter, 550 horsepower V8 engine.
snippet: The Jaguar produces a thrilling growl from its supercharged 5-liter, 550 horsepower V8 engine.
lead_paragraph: PATRONS of the arts should love the Jaguar F-Type coupe as much as auto enthusiasts. As sculpture, it’s as much Rodin as road machine, with undulating aluminum panels draped over a bonded and riveted aluminum platform. Originally shown as the C-X16 concept drawn by Jaguar’s design director, Ian Callum, the production version remains remarkably true to his vision.

headline.main: Video Review: The Jaguar F-Type R Conducts Its Own Symphony
headline.print_headline: A Supercharged Jaguar Conducts Its Own Symphony
